The Osun State Government has commenced the decontamination exercise at public places to curb the spread of COVID-19. Environment and Sanitation Commissioner Sola Oladepo said since the beginning of the exercise, the decontamination team had fumigated and disinfected more than 1,800 public and private schools. His words: â€œThe Osun State government has embarked on decontamination exercise in all nooks and crannies of the state to prevent the spread of COVID-19 pandemic as well as to ensure that its citizens are in good health.